cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.CR

This paper deals with mobile traffic analytics, which is a subfield of computer networking (cs.NI). The proposed technique involves deep learning and neural networks (cs.LG), specifically the use of a Generative Adversarial Network (GAN). The paper also draws inspiration from image processing (cs.CV) and involves spatial aggregation of measurements (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations and security concerns of existing traffic monitoring techniques (cs.CR).
